cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.SD

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the folding of plane graphs, which is a topic in computational geometry. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents algorithms for testing flat foldability and counting the number of distinct folded states. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with graph theory and combinatorics. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the characterization of flat-foldable plane graphs, which can be seen as a game-theoretic problem. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is unlikely as it is not related to the content of the paper.
